<!--91-->They Are Coming x 3    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">With only 60 cards and an insane card-drawing engine behind the deck, you should easily be able to run clear through this deck before site 7.<br />
The real trick is to try to play a whole lotta orcs and the Balrog at site 5, which usually means death for anyone. And don&#39;t give me that &quot;Power According to his Stature&quot; crap. Dealing withs PAthS is as simple as overwhelming everyone else your opponent has, then letting your Balrog finish his or her Frodo.<br />
But this is a fun deck, and the fun comes in on your fellowship side. I love pipe decks, and with the new pipes in Elf Lords you can spot up to 7 pipes at a time by exerting Gimli. This means that with six pipeweed cards you can use a maximum of 42 effects (7 per pipeweed * 6 pipeweeds = 42). That&#39;s up to 42 wounds healed or 42 twilight removed from the pool, or even up to 42 burden&#39;s removed from your Ringbearer.<br />
The rest of the free peoples deck is character specific equipment and the cart. YOU NEED THE CART! Do whatever it takes to go first so you can play your cart from the deck.<br />
<br />
A few notes on cards I used (or didn&#39;t use):<br />
The Grey Pilgrim: Card drawing engine. I need that more than I need a 10-strength Gandalf.<br />
No Aragorn: With a 60 card limit I chose only to play as many companions as I had Pipes, and Boromir&#39;s ability to avoid overwhelming more than any of the abilities of the various Aragorns.<br />
Sleep Caradhras: Two words; Condition Removal<br />
<br />
Well, that&#39;s my non-strategy for the deck. I hope you enjoyed reading it as much as I enjoyed writing it. I appreciate any input you may have on the deck. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
